{{Han compound|口|令|t1=mouth|ls=psc|c1=s|c2=p}}. Doublet of {{och-l|呤}}.

===Etymology===
Related to {{och-l|令|to order; to command; order}} ({{zh-ref|Wang, 1982}}). Both may be derived from {{och-l|名|name}}: “name” ({{lang|zh|名}}) > “to name; to give (a name to)” ({{lang|zh|命}}) > “to order; to command” > “order; command” > “destiny; fate; lot” > “life” ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}). For a roughly similar semantic development, see Latin {{m|la|fāta}} (whence English {{m|en|fate}}), from {{m|la|fātus||spoken}}, from {{m|la|for||to speak}}.

