===Etymology 1===
{{ja-kanjitab|yomi=k|いのち}}
From {{inh|ja|ojp|-|sort=いのち}}, from {{inh|ja|jpx-pro|*inəti|sort=いのち}}. Probably a compound of Old Japanese elements {{compound|ja|sort=いのち|息|tr1=i|t1=breath|pos1=''i'' in compounds, ''iki'' on its own|の|tr2=no|pos2=possessive particle|霊|tr3=chi|t3=spirit, force, soul}}.<ref>{{R:ja:SMKGGJT|p=91}}</ref>

Some analyses describe this as a compound using {{m|ja|生|tr=i||life, breath|pos=''i'' in compounds, ''iki'' on its own}} as the initial semantic element. This is equally valid, as {{m|ja|息|tr=iki}} and {{m|ja|生き|tr=iki}} are cognates.

